The article is a joint declaration in commemoration of the 60th anniversary of the alliance between the Republic of Korea (ROK) and the United States of America. The U.S.-ROK alliance has served as an anchor for stability, security, and prosperity on the Korean Peninsula and in the Asia-Pacific region for six decades. The two leaders, President Barack Obama and President Park Geun-hye, affirm that the alliance is well-placed to address the opportunities and challenges of the future. The alliance has evolved into a comprehensive strategic partnership that extends beyond security to include political, economic, cultural, and people-to-people cooperation. The United States remains committed to the defense of the Republic of Korea, including through extended deterrence and a full range of military capabilities. The article also highlights the positive results of the U.S.-Korea Free Trade Agreement (KORUS FTA) and the progress made in realizing the 2009 Joint Vision for the Alliance. The two nations are determined to achieve the peaceful denuclearization of North Korea and are working with other partners to ensure compliance with international obligations. The article emphasizes the importance of regional and global security, economic growth, and cooperation in addressing common challenges. Finally, it highlights the strong relationship between the peoples of the United States and the Republic of Korea and the efforts to further strengthen ties between the societies.